The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Viru: Wasnt under pressure
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Viru: Wasnt under pressure
            A CORRESPONDENT                      
	Galle: Virender Sehwag said on Sunday that he was under no pressure to perform after his failure in the first Test in Colombo. The vice-captain contributed 25 and 13 in the Test that India lost by an innings and 239 runs.         
	He felt captain Anil Kumble and coach Gary Kirstens backing helped him earn the Man of the Match in the second Test. After an unbeaten 201 in the first innings, he scored a 50 in his second knock.         
	I was under no pressure The captain and coach backed me and asked me to enjoy myself That gave me the confidence, said Sehwag.         
	Asked if he was determined to play a long innings here, Sehwag said: I had failed in the last couple of innings and so had to come good here I am happy                                                                                                                          
